---
const faqs = [
  {
    question: '"Don\'t these cameras only catch criminals?"',
    lead: '99.5% of the plates Flock scans belong to people not suspected of anything.',
    rest: 'Flock\'s cameras don\'t just record plate numbers. They log vehicle make, color, and travel patterns for every car that passes. That\'s a record of where everyone goes.',
    source: 'Source: <a href="https://www.eff.org/pages/automated-license-plate-readers-alpr" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-[#fbbf24] hover:underline">EFF</a>',
  },
  {
    question: '"If you have nothing to hide, why worry?"',
    lead: 'The 4th Amendment protects everyone from government searches without cause, not just people with something to hide.',
    rest: 'These cameras log every trip your family makes. Every school run. Every doctor visit. Every church service. All of it goes into a government database, whether you\'ve done anything wrong or not.',
  },
  {
    question: '"Doesn\'t this reduce crime?"',
    lead: 'Austin ran its own city audit and couldn\'t find evidence the cameras reduce crime.',
    rest: 'These systems cost cities hundreds of thousands of dollars a year. Greenville paid with federal civil asset forfeiture money that bypassed normal council appropriations. We want public safety too. Show us the return on that investment.',
    source: 'Source: <a href="https://www.eff.org/deeplinks/2025/06/victory-austin-organizers-cancel-citys-flock-alpr-contract" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-[#fbbf24] hover:underline">EFF</a> <span class="mx-1">&middot;</span> <a href="https://www.kut.org/austin/2025-06-04/austin-tx-automatic-license-reader-program-police-data-privacy-flock" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-[#fbbf24] hover:underline">KUT Radio</a>',
  },
  {
    question: '"Isn\'t the data protected?"',
    lead: 'Flock couldn\'t even explain how data sharing got turned back on in Ventura County after the agency disabled it.',
    rest: 'Right here in SC, a law enforcement officer used SLED\'s database to look up his own car, then changed the record. When a reporter asked SLED about misconduct, they refused to answer. That\'s what protected looks like in practice.',
    source: 'Sources: <a href="https://www.cbsnews.com/losangeles/news/flock-license-plate-readers-shared-data-with-out-of-state-federal-agencies/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-[#fbbf24] hover:underline">CBS Los Angeles</a> <span class="mx-1">&middot;</span> <a href="https://www.postandcourier.com/news/alpr-cameras-south-carolina-flock-safety-license-plate-readers/article_787a262a-dbd2-11ee-a901-634acead588b.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-[#fbbf24] hover:underline">Post and Courier</a>',
  },
  {
    question: '"Isn\'t this anti-police?"',
    lead: 'A Virginia police chief with 41 years on the job helped cancel his city\'s Flock contract.',
    rest: 'Chief Jim Williams of Staunton called residents raising privacy concerns "democracy in action." Back home, conservative Republican Rep. Garry Smith of Simpsonville has the same concern: "I\'ve run into individuals in law enforcement who have taken advantage of their positions. The potential is certainly out there."',
    source: 'Sources: <a href="https://augustafreepress.com/news/staunton-to-cancel-flock-safety-camera-contract-doesnt-agree-with-ideology-of-ceo/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-[#fbbf24] hover:underline">Augusta Free Press</a> <span class="mx-1">&middot;</span> <a href="https://www.postandcourier.com/greenville/news/greenville-adding-more-cameras-to-read-license-plates-raising-questions-of-oversight-privacy/article_4cf2761a-4157-11eb-98b9-9b7e9434164e.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-[#fbbf24] hover:underline">Post and Courier</a>',
  },
];
---

<section id="faq" aria-labelledby="faq-heading" class="bg-[#171717] py-20 md:py-28">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6">
    <h2 id="faq-heading" class="text-white font-extrabold text-2xl md:text-4xl tracking-[-0.02em] mb-10">
      But what about&hellip;
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-3">
      {faqs.map((faq, i) => (
        <details class="faq-item group border-l-[3px] border-[#262626]" data-faq={i} open={i === 0 || undefined}>
          <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer py-4 px-5 list-none [&::-webkit-details-marker]:hidden">
            <span class="text-white font-bold text-base pr-4">{faq.question}</span>
            <span class="faq-icon text-[#ef4444] font-bold text-xl flex-shrink-0 transition-transform duration-300">+</span>
          </summary>
          <div class="faq-content">
            <div class="faq-inner px-5 pb-5">
              <p class="text-[#a3a3a3] text-base leading-[1.7]"><strong class="text-[#d4d4d4]">{faq.lead}</strong> {faq.rest}</p>
              {faq.source && (
                <p class="text-[#525252] text-xs mt-2" set:html={faq.source} />
              )}
            </div>
          </div>
        </details>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  /* Smooth open/close animation using grid trick */
  .faq-content {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-rows: 0fr;
    transition: grid-template-rows 300ms ease-out;
  }

  .faq-inner {
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  details[open] .faq-content {
    grid-template-rows: 1fr;
  }

  /* Red border when open */
  details[open] {
    border-color: #ef4444;
  }

  /* Rotate + to x (toggle indicator) */
  details[open] .faq-icon {
    transform: rotate(45deg);
  }

  /* Prevent instant close — handled by JS */
  details.closing .faq-content {
    grid-template-rows: 0fr;
  }

  details.closing {
    border-color: #262626;
  }

  details.closing .faq-icon {
    transform: rotate(0deg);
  }
</style>

<script>
  // Handle smooth close animation for <details> elements
  document.querySelectorAll('.faq-item').forEach(details => {
    const summary = details.querySelector('summary');

    summary?.addEventListener('click', (e) => {
      // If currently open, animate close
      if (details.hasAttribute('open')) {
        e.preventDefault();
        details.classList.add('closing');

        // Wait for animation to finish, then actually close
        setTimeout(() => {
          details.classList.remove('closing');
          details.removeAttribute('open');
        }, 300);
      }
    });
  });
</script>
